# Complete Implementation

```cpp
#include <hexi/static_buffer.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>
#include <algorithm>

template<size_t buffer_size = 1024>
std::vector<uint8_t> preview_buffer_data(const hexi::static_buffer<std::byte, buffer_size>& buffer, size_t bytes_to_preview) {
    // Get the available data size
    size_t available = buffer.size();
    size_t to_copy = std::min(bytes_to_preview, available);

    // Create result vector
    std::vector<uint8_t> result;
    result.reserve(to_copy);

    // Get the data buffer(s) - buffer.data() returns readable buffers
    // without modifying the read position
    auto data = buffer.data();

    // Copy bytes to result
    // The buffer may be split into multiple segments due to circular nature
    size_t copied = 0;
    for (const auto& buf : data) {
        if (copied >= to_copy) break;

        // Get pointer to the buffer data
        const auto* ptr = static_cast<const std::byte*>(buf.data());
        size_t buf_size = buf.size();
        size_t to_copy_from_buf = std::min(buf_size, to_copy - copied);

        // Copy bytes from this buffer segment
        for (size_t i = 0; i < to_copy_from_buf; ++i) {
            result.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(ptr[i]));
        }

        copied += to_copy_from_buf;
    }

    return result;
}
```

## Key Implementation Details:

1. **Non-destructive read**: Uses `buffer.data()` which returns readable data without calling `consume()`, preserving the read pointer position.

2. **Size checking**: Uses `buffer.size()` to determine available bytes and limits copying to the minimum of requested and available bytes.

3. **Circular buffer handling**: Iterates through potentially multiple buffer segments (since circular buffers may have data split at the wrap-around point).

4. **Type conversion**: Converts from `std::byte` to `uint8_t` during the copy operation.

5. **Efficiency**: Pre-reserves vector capacity to avoid reallocation during data copying.

